parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Water Pump and Engine Block Cracking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty water pump can cause coolant to leak into the engine oil, leading to engine damage and potential failure, which can cause the vehicle to stall or decelerate suddenly, increasing the risk of accidents.
The fuel leak can cause a fire hazard, and the fuel smell inside the vehicle can lead to health problems for the occupants.
The failure of the camshaft can cause engine stalling, misfiring, and deceleration, increasing the risk of accidents.

The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, hesitate, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also cause injury or death, especially when trying to merge into traffic.
symptoms: The transmission jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle fails to shift into gear
the transmission slips or skips gears
the vehicle feels stuck in gear

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank and Fuel System Component Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank and fuel system components can cause a strong fuel odor, which can lead to discomfort, distraction, and potential health risks for drivers and passengers. Additionally, it can result in poor gas mileage and decreased vehicle performance.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor inside the vehicle
particularly at the front of the vehicle
and outside the vehicle; poor gas mileage; inability to drive without opening windows.
